    "summary": "ona.com exposes a documented HTTP API, a SCIM provisioning API, and an `ona` CLI; authentication is via Ona-issued personal access tokens for the API/CLI and a separate SCIM bearer token for SCIM.",
    "description": "Ona is a platform for running autonomous software-engineering agents and development environments in the cloud or inside a customer's VPC. It provides managed environments, automations, identity features, and integrations around source-control-driven software work.",
    "credentials": {
      "ona_pat": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Personal access token",
        "generateUrl": "https://app.ona.com/settings/personal-access-tokens",
        "setup": "Go to [Personal access tokens](https://app.ona.com/settings/personal-access-tokens), click **New Token**, choose an expiration and access level (**Read-only** or **Read & Write**), then create and copy the token. Ona documents PATs as the way to authenticate the [CLI](https://ona.com/docs/ona/integrations/cli) and [SDK](https://ona.com/docs/ona/integrations/sdk).",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "ona_scim_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "SCIM bearer token",
        "setup": "In Ona, go to **Organization Settings → Login and Security** and open **SCIM Provisioning**. Create a SCIM configuration linked to an existing SSO provider; Ona then displays a SCIM endpoint URL and a bearer token. Copy the token immediately because the docs say it is shown only once. See [SCIM Provisioning](https://ona.com/docs/ona/scim/overview).",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
